Anglo Platinum, Impala and FirstRand May Move: South Africa Stocks Preview

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-03-28T05:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/anglo-platinum-pallinghurst-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell 51.8,
or 0.2 percent, to 31,595.89 in Johannesburg.  Anglo Platinum Ltd. (AMS)  : Zimbabwe ordered foreign mine
operators, which also includes  Aquarius Platinum Ltd. (AQP)  
and  Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd. (IMP)  , to explain within 45
days how they will meet government demands to sell 51 percent of
their local assets to “indigenous” people. Anglo Platinum’s
stock rose 0.1 percent to 679.37 rand, Impala fell 1.2 percent
to 197.58 rand and Aquarius added 1.2 percent to 41 rand.  Anooraq Resources Corp. (ARQ)  : The precious-metals
producer had its rating cut to “sector perform” from
“outperform” by  Leon Esterhuizen , an analyst at Royal Bank of
 Canada . The stock slid 3.5 percent to 1.11 rand.  ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. (ACL)  : The steelmaker
said it plans to proceed with the acquisition of Imperial Crown
Trading 289 Ltd., which was awarded the right to a portion of
Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.’s Sishen mine, denying a report by the
Johannesburg-based Sunday Times that it was considering pulling
out of the deal. The shares fell 1 cent to 87 rand.  FirstRand Bank Ltd. (FSR SJ): The South African bank signed
$150 million of syndicated loans with companies including China
Construction Bank Corp. and Bank of Taiwan in Taipei, the
Economic Daily News reported, without saying where it got the
information. FirstRand declined 0.9 percent to 19.28 rand.  Pallinghurst Resources Ltd. (PGL)  : The commodities
investment company will report its annual earnings. The stock
price dropped 7 cents, or 1.7 percent, to 4.02 rand.  The following shares begin trading without the rights to
their latest dividends:  AVI Ltd. (AVI SJ), Amalgamated Appliance Holding (AMA SJ),
Anglo American Plc (AGL SJ), Astrapak Ltd. (APK SJ), Bidvest
Group Ltd. (BVT SJ), Clover Industries Ltd. (CLR SJ), Fairvest
Property Holdings Ltd. (FVT SJ),  FirstRand Ltd. (FSR)  , MMI
Holdings Ltd. (MMI SJ), MTN Group Ltd. (MTN SJ), Racec Group
Ltd. (RAC SJ), RMB Holdings Ltd. (RMH SJ), RMI Holdings (RMI
SJ), Sasfin Holdings Ltd. (SFN SJ), Trencor Ltd. (TRE SJ).  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY)   increased 0.4 percent to
$25.68. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) climbed 0.3 percent to
$46.65. BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) dropped 1.3 percent to
$75.30.  DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY)   gained 0.2 percent to $4.99.
Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI US) fell 1.2 percent to $16.82. Harmony
Gold Mining Co. (HMY US) declined 2 percent to $14.10. Impala
Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US) dropped 2 percent to $28.31.  Sappi
Ltd. (SPP)   slipped 0.2 percent to $5.05.  Sasol Ltd. (SSL)  
climbed 0.2 percent to $55.14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
